  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2009-09-25",
    "date": "2009-12-08T23:08:26Z",
    "text": "Hurricane Satellite Modernization Act - Authorizes the Administrator of National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) to procure and launch the next-generation Extended Ocean Vector Winds Mission, or XOVWM, constellation of satellites.\n\nRequires the Administrator to coordinate with the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) to ensure that the capabilities of the XOVWM constellation of satellites will meet the operational data needs of NOAA.\n\nRequires development of a plan and schedule for the procurement and launch of the XOVWM constellation of satellites.\n\nAuthorizes the Administrator of NOAA to operate the constellation of satellites procured under this Act."
  },
